Chronic oral administration of diltiazem hydrochloride to patients in doses of up to 540 mg/day has resulted in small increases in PR interval and on occasion produces abnormal prolongation (see 
                              WARNINGS
                           ).

In an in vitro dissolution study, the release rate of diltiazem from diltiazem hydrochloride extended-release capsules increased significantly as the alcohol percentage in the dissolution medium increased. The effect of alcohol on the release rate may lead to a change in the pharmacokinetics of diltiazem, such as a more rapid absorption and/or an increase in the systemic exposure of diltiazem (see 
                              PRECAUTIONS, Drug Interactions
                           ).

Gastrointestinal: Anorexia, constipation, diarrhea, dry mouth, dysgeusia, dyspepsia, mild elevations of SGOT, SGPT, LDH, and alkaline phosphatase (see 

      WARNINGS, Acute Hepatic Injury

), thirst, vomiting, weight increase.
